        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 3:58PM CDT until June 8 at 4:30PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Arcadia, or 9
miles south of Fort Scott, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Prairie State Park, Mulberry, Arcadia, Bronaugh, Burgess, Croweburg,
Oskaloosa, Pawnee Station, Hiattville, Farlington, Garland,
Englevale, and Hannon.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

This is a dangerous storm, capable of producing large hail driven by
severe winds! SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy structure and stay
away from windows! If you are caught outdoors, cover your head and
neck.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
